Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.86,0:01:04.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢大家 你们好\N{\fs90}Thank you, everybody! Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.63,0:01:07.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\fs90}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.94,0:01:10.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢你们的热情\N{\fs90}Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.86,0:01:16.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常感谢\N{\fs90}Thank you, everybody. Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.89,0:01:18.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里是The Grand Tour\N{\fs90}This is The Grand Tour,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.59,0:01:21.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,这周 我们回家了\N{\fs90}and this week... we've come home!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.58,0:01:27.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们回来啦 我们又回到英国了\N{\fs90}We're back! We're back in Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.37,0:01:30.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,准确地说 我们现在在约克郡\N{\fs90}We're actually in Yorkshire, which is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.08,0:01:33.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\fs90}There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.41,0:01:36.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,也正是我们仨长大的地方\N{\fs90}Which is where all three of us grew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.30,0:01:38.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,-确切的讲  -惠特比\N{\fs90}- Specifically-- Yeah, specifically... Whitby!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.85,0:01:42.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,确切的讲 我们正在惠特比的渔港 后面就是\N{\fs90}We're in the fishing port of Whitby. There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.07,0:01:49.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然 惠特比因为其不可思议的炸鱼薯条\N{\fs90}Now, Whitby, of course, is famous all around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.27,0:01:51.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,而闻名世界\N{\fs90}for its unbelievable fish and chips.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.95,0:01:53.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,和 scraps\N{\fs90}- With scraps.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.10,0:01:55.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\fs90}You what?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.68,0:01:57.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,炸鱼薯条和 scraps 每次里面都有 scraps\N{\fs90}Fish and chips with scraps. You get scraps.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.84,0:02:00.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是那些黏在锅底的面糊\N{\fs90}Little bits of batter that stay in the bottom of the fryer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.49,0:02:01.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,-对啊 scraps -不对 那叫 bits\N{\fs90}-Yeah, scraps. -No, they're bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.87,0:02:04.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,-炸鱼薯片和bits -不 scraps\N{\fs90}-Fish and chips with bits. -No, it's scraps.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.89,0:02:08.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是 bits\N{\fs90}It is bits! Bits!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.74,0:02:10.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,这样 觉得应该叫 bits 的举手\N{\fs90}Right, hands up for bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.85,0:02:12.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,-大错特错  -支持 scraps 的举手\N{\fs90}- Wrong! - Scraps?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.42,0:02:16.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,-看 就叫 scraps -别和我争\N{\fs90}-See, it's scraps. -Don't argue with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.69,0:02:19.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我出生在约克郡\N{\fs90}Because I was born in Yorkshire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.92,0:02:23.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,从17世纪起 我家族里的每一个人都住在这里\N{\fs90}Every single one of my family back to the 17th century's from Yorkshire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.34,0:02:25.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,我是世界上血统最纯正的约克郡人\N{\fs90}I'm the most Yorkshire person in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.40,0:02:27.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,是吗 有意思了\N{\fs90}You know, it's funny,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.14,0:02:29.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为根本看不出来 完全没法分辨\N{\fs90}cos you can't tell. You really wouldn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.62,0:02:32.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,约克郡人是出名的心直口快\N{\fs90}- Yorkshire people are famous for speaking their mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.02,0:02:34.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,但你...我们就...\N{\fs90}And when you... We...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.78,0:02:37.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们永远不知道你在想什么 这简直\N{\fs90}We never know what you're thinking. It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.17,0:02:38.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,猜猜我现在在想什么\N{\fs90}What am I thinking now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.84,0:02:40.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,你在想 自己真是才华横溢\N{\fs90}You're thinking you're brilliant
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.55,0:02:42.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我就是个烦人的小矮子\N{\fs90}and I'm an irritating little short-arse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.58,0:02:45.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你怎么猜到的  -怎么说\N{\fs90}-How did you know? -Yeah, it's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.78,0:02:47.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这简直不可思议  -是的 我会读心术 同志\N{\fs90}-It's incredible! -Yeah, I'm psychic, mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.05,0:02:51.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,约克郡的板球也很出名 这没意思\N{\fs90}Other things Yorkshire's cricket. That's not interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.78,0:02:55.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有个电视剧 最后的夏日美酒\N{\fs90}Ooh, and then there was a TV show called Last Of The Summer Wine,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.17,0:02:58.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,讲述了三个衣着丑陋的老男人的故事\N{\fs90}which was about three very badly dressed old men
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.24,0:03:00.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们总是碰壁\N{\fs90}who fell over,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.64,0:03:03.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,总能办砸每件事\N{\fs90}and everything they ever did went wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.68,0:03:05.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,-太烂了  -没法看\N{\fs90}- It was rubbish. - Yeah, terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.18,0:03:06.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,完全不知道他们怎么火的\N{\fs90}I don't know why that took off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.80,0:03:08.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,约克郡的造车业\N{\fs90}Erm... Carmaking?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.55,0:03:09.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,这么说吧\N{\fs90}Well, let's put it this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.77,0:03:11.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,不能说这是英岛的底特律\N{\fs90}It's not exactly the Detroit of the British Isles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.51,0:03:13.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,确实不能\N{\fs90}No, it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.34,0:03:16.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,但本周这却有许多和车有关的活动\N{\fs90}But there is a lot of motoring-related stuff here this week,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.68,0:03:18.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我们来了\N{\fs90}because we're in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.69,0:03:23.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 让我们开始今天的节目吧\N{\fs90}So, let's get on with the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.53,0:03:25.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,开始吧\N{\fs90}Yes, let's.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.90,0:03:29.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们得从维多利亚时代说起\N{\fs90}We begin in Victorian times,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.52,0:03:32.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,那时詹姆斯梅还是个年轻老太婆\N{\fs90}when James May was a little old lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.10,0:03:36.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,当时 有钱的男士...\N{\fs90}You see, back then, gentlemen of means--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.58,0:03:38.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,也就是穿着花呢西装的有钱人\N{\fs90}-Rich people in tweed suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.01,0:03:39.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 穿着花呢西装的有钱人\N{\fs90}-Yes, rich people in tweed suits
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:42.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们会进行所谓的大壮游\N{\fs90}would take what was known as the Grand Tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.87,0:03:44.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,去到法国或意大利\N{\fs90}They'd go off to France or Italy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.93,0:03:47.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,花几个月学习当地的文化\N{\fs90}and they'd spend a few months learning about culture
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.94,0:03:49.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,酒和音乐\N{\fs90}and wine and music.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.61,0:03:52.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,而现在 大家去的是马盖鲁夫\N{\fs90}Nowadays, of course, everybody goes to Magaluf
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.33,0:03:55.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,在那学习喝酒 醉吐 然后滥交\N{\fs90}and learns about beer and vomit and chlamydia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.72,0:03:56.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,世风日下\N{\fs90}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.53,0:03:58.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们觉得这很可惜\N{\fs90}Now, we think this is a real shame,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.84,0:04:00.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以杰瑞米和我去到了意大利\N{\fs90}so Jeremy and I went off to Italy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.68,0:04:04.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,进行了自己现代意义上的大壮游\N{\fs90}to do our own modern take on the Grand Tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.13,0:04:06.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是一段淋漓尽致启迪人心的旅程\N{\fs90}A wonderful, inspirational journey
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.58,0:04:08.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,不仅最后成为了我们节目名字\N{\fs90}that not only gave its name to this show,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.66,0:04:11.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,还成了数千台GT车的名字\N{\fs90}but also to 1,000 GT cars:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.79,0:04:13.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,豪华旅行车\N{\fs90}grand tourers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.65,0:04:23.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们从托斯卡纳山顶城市 锡耶纳 出发\N{\fs90}Our start point was the Tuscan hilltop city of Siena.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.66,0:04:29.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是世界上最激动人心的赛马比赛发源地\N{\fs90}Home to the most exciting horse race in the world:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.97,0:04:31.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,派力奥赛马节\N{\fs90}the Palio.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.96,0:04:44.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,看那匹马 太棒了\N{\fs90}Look at that! Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.40,0:04:48.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,这应是一段精彩的\N{\fs90}It was the beginning of what would be a very fabulous
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.70,0:04:50.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,文化之旅的开端\N{\fs90}and very cultured journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.11,0:04:55.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们沿途会游览美丽的佛罗伦萨\N{\fs90}We'd visit the magnificent cities of Florence
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.45,0:04:56.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,博洛尼亚和维罗纳\N{\fs90}and Bologna and Verona
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.04,0:04:59.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,直到终点\N{\fs90}on our way to the finishing point
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.20,0:05:02.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,这其中最宏伟的城市\N{\fs90}in the most magnificent city of them all:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.39,0:05:03.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,威尼斯\N{\fs90}Venice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.05,0:05:07.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们开的车也丝毫不逊色\N{\fs90}The cars we'd be driving were fabulous, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.20,0:05:11.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯选择了劳斯莱斯曜影\N{\fs90}James had chosen the Rolls-Royce Dawn,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.46,0:05:14.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,也就是古斯特的双门敞篷版\N{\fs90}a new two-door, drop-head version of the Ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.93,0:05:18.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,我选了DB11\N{\fs90}And I'd be in the DB11,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.27,0:05:21.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,阿斯顿马丁优雅美丽的豪华旅行车系列\N{\fs90}the latest in a long line
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.75,0:05:24.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,之中的最新款\N{\fs90}of elegant and beautiful Aston Martin grand tourers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.27,0:05:28.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,它的后视镜都如此有美感\N{\fs90}Even its door mirrors are beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.50,0:05:30.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,它的车轮也这么美\N{\fs90}Its wheels are beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.31,0:05:31.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,这真是...\N{\fs90}This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.78,0:05:35.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,这真是我见过最漂亮的车之一\N{\fs90}This is one of the most beautiful cars I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.73,0:05:37.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,可惜是棕色的\N{\fs90}Shame it's brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.31,0:05:39.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这不是棕色  -怎么不是\N{\fs90}-It isn't brown! -Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.37,0:05:41.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是日落橙\N{\fs90}It isn't brown! It's Sunset Orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.61,0:05:44.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,这要不是棕色 那我的车就是绿色\N{\fs90}It's not brown in the way that my car is green.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.29,0:05:45.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是棕色\N{\fs90}It's brown.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.63,0:05:48.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的车实际就是敞篷版的宝马7系\N{\fs90}Your car is a convertible BMW 7 Series.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.36,0:05:49.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,才不是\N{\fs90}No, it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.06,0:05:51.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,这底下不就是宝马7系吗\N{\fs90}But is it a 7 Series underneath?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.53,0:05:53.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-有点共用的底盘件 -所以嘛\N{\fs90}-Bits of the floor panel. -There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.85,0:05:56.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,一辆230多万的敞篷宝马7系\N{\fs90}￡265,000 for a convertible 7 Series.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.67,0:05:57.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,才不是\N{\fs90}It isn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.81,0:05:59.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你要在意大利自驾游\N{\fs90}If you're going to drive across Italy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:01.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,学习当地文化\N{\fs90}which we're going to do, taking in some culture...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.53,0:06:03.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,-怎么  -得开这样的车\N{\fs90}-Mm-hm. -...that's what you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.25,0:06:05.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,-开辆棕色的车吗  -这不是棕色\N{\fs90}-A brown car? -It isn't brown!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.20,0:06:08.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,-就是棕色  -我们也别争了\N{\fs90}-It's brown! -Look, let's not bicker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.55,0:06:11.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们出发吧\N{\fs90}Actually, on this occasion, let's get on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.85,0:06:13.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们俩要开车穿越\N{\fs90}We are both going to drive across
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.66,0:06:16.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,我认为是咱们最喜欢的国家\N{\fs90}what is, I think, our favourite country in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.69,0:06:20.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,享受文化 美酒\N{\fs90}enjoy some culture, enjoy some fine wine,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.23,0:06:21.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,美食 艺术...\N{\fs90}some food, some art, some...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.67,0:06:25.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是谁\N{\fs90}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.90,0:06:30.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,-那是哈蒙德吗  -不好意思 我迟到了\N{\fs90}-Is that Hammond? -Sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:32.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们不知道你会来\N{\fs90}We didn't know you were coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.43,0:06:33.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们也不希望你会来\N{\fs90}We rather hoped you weren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.44,0:06:35.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我就来了 看看我选的车\N{\fs90}Well, I am, and look at the car I've brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.89,0:06:39.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,道奇挑战者SRT地狱猫\N{\fs90}Dodge Challenger SRT Hellcat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.48,0:06:41.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,707匹马力\N{\fs90}707 American horsepower,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.95,0:06:44.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,扭矩力大到可以拉倒那座老房子\N{\fs90}and enough torque to pull that old building down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.93,0:06:46.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,别 那老房子可是...\N{\fs90}Just... That "old building" is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.89,0:06:48.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,算了 和你讲不清\N{\fs90}Oh, well, never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.16,0:06:52.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 在托斯卡纳不适合开肌肉车\N{\fs90}Hammond, Tuscany, not really the home of the muscle car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.52,0:06:56.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,我就是担心你俩会这么无聊严肃\N{\fs90}Yeah, you see, I was worried you two were gonna be all boring and serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.29,0:06:58.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,我就是来确保这是段有趣的旅程\N{\fs90}And I am here to make sure this trip is fun
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.70,0:07:01.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,别告诉我 最开始的大壮游并不有趣\N{\fs90}because don't tell me the original Grand Tour wasn't fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.18,0:07:03.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,那就是18世纪的炮弹飞车\N{\fs90}It was like an 18th century Cannonball Run,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.75,0:07:06.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,只是大家打的是传统吗啡 而不是可卡因\N{\fs90}only with old-fashioned morphine instead of cocaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.07,0:07:07.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,开这车来 才合适\N{\fs90}This is gonna be brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.69,0:07:09.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,你车上的广告怎么回事\N{\fs90}What's with your advertising?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.13,0:07:11.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为美国人以前做壮游时\N{\fs90}Well, because the Americans used to do the Grand Tour,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.45,0:07:12.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,都会找赞助商承担开销\N{\fs90}and they used to get sponsors to help cover the costs,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.84,0:07:15.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我也给自己找了些赞助\N{\fs90}so I've got myself some sponsorship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.48,0:07:16.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,波比的... 什么是grit\N{\fs90}What, Bobby's... What is a grit?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.05,0:07:18.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是... 大概...\N{\fs90}That's a... It's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.55,0:07:20.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,好像是咖啡渣或者土豆泥\N{\fs90}a bit left over after coffee or potatoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.56,0:07:22.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我没听说过  -如广告所示\N{\fs90}-I don't know. -Well, it's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.32,0:07:24.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,牛仔润滑油改装厂\N{\fs90}"Rodeo Lube 'N' Tune."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.21,0:07:26.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,润滑油改装厂 厉害吧\N{\fs90}"Lube 'N' Tune." Yep, look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.78,0:07:28.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,别人一看我这\N{\fs90}The things is, people will look at me in that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.56,0:07:30.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,就知道我在大壮游\N{\fs90}and know I am on a Grand Tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.43,0:07:32.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们呢 他们会觉得 这两个傻犊子在干什么\N{\fs90}You, they'll think, "What are these two old farts doing?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.88,0:07:35.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,-说真的...  -你什么都没准备\N{\fs90}- Seriously-- - You have made no effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.17,0:07:36.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,连情绪都没酝酿好\N{\fs90}You haven't got into the mood for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.84,0:07:39.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,艺术 音乐 文化\N{\fs90}Art, music, culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.74,0:07:41.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,-精致  -对\N{\fs90}- Refinement. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.20,0:07:43.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是你的吗\N{\fs90}Is this something to do with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.72,0:07:44.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 他们来了\N{\fs90}Yes. Yes, they're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.00,0:07:46.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我的备胎\N{\fs90}These are my spare tyres.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.42,0:07:49.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,这次旅程路途遥远\N{\fs90}Because on a trip like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.55,0:07:52.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且车的马力扭矩太大\N{\fs90}in a car with that much power and that much torque,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.06,0:07:53.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,我需要这么多备胎\N{\fs90}I am gonna get through some tyres.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.57,0:07:55.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,-小心树  -不管了\N{\fs90}-Tree. -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.93,0:08:01.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的后备箱可装不下这么多胎\N{\fs90}That lot was not gonna fit in the boot, or trunk, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.86,0:08:05.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,这才是奢华 这才是大壮游\N{\fs90}That is luxury! That is grand touring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.10,0:08:09.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们只能不情愿地让乡巴佬同事加入\N{\fs90}Reluctantly, we agreed to let our vulgar colleague tag along.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.05,0:08:34.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 你在故意制造噪音\N{\fs90}Hammond, you're deliberately making an irritating noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.10,0:08:35.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,消停会 行吗\N{\fs90}Please stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.44,0:08:37.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是故意的\N{\fs90}I am, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.09,0:08:46.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,我承认 哈蒙德的道奇地狱猫是一辆好车\N{\fs90}I will freely admit that Hammond's Dodge Hellcat is a remarkable car.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.29,0:08:52.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我们是在密尔沃基参加拉力赛 这车再合适不过\N{\fs90}It would be perfect if we were at a tractor pull in Milwaukee.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.06,0:08:54.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我们在这\N{\fs90}But we're not. We're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.01,0:08:58.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是托斯卡纳\N{\fs90}And here in Tuscany...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.29,0:09:03.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,你需要辆这个\N{\fs90}...you need one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.39,0:09:18.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是DB9的全新替代车型\N{\fs90}This is the all-new replacement for the DB9,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.12,0:09:21.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,用在此再合适不过\N{\fs90}and it is the perfect car for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.94,0:09:25.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,它甚至配备了三种驾驶模式\N{\fs90}It even comes with three running modes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.57,0:09:28.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,运动模式 运动+模式\N{\fs90}You've got Sport, Sport Plus,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.22,0:09:30.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有个我即将用到的\N{\fs90}and the one I'm gonna use.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.32,0:09:32.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,GT模式\N{\fs90}GT.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.94,0:09:34.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,壮游天地间\N{\fs90}Grand Touring.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.45,0:09:41.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,前面 是一个5.2双涡轮V12引擎\N{\fs90}Up front, there's a 5.2 litre, twin-turbocharged V12
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.50,0:09:44.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,能迸发出600匹马力\N{\fs90}which produces 600 horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.30,0:09:47.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,且马力均匀\N{\fs90}And they are smooth horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.88,0:09:51.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,如梦似幻\N{\fs90}Dreamy horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.63,0:09:59.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快 你就能买到这车的低配版\N{\fs90}In the fullness of time, you'll be able to buy a cheaper version of this car
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.32,0:10:01.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,配有AMG的V8引擎\N{\fs90}with an AMG V8.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.79,0:10:05.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,也是阿斯顿马丁与奔驰合作的产物\N{\fs90}It's all part of a deal that Aston have done with Mercedes,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.14,0:10:07.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,你已经可以看到其结果如何\N{\fs90}and you can see evidence of the deal already.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.27,0:10:10.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车有奔驰的换挡杆 奔驰的电子系统\N{\fs90}This has got Mercedes switchgear, Mercedes electronics.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.16,0:10:12.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,甚至连导航都是奔驰的\N{\fs90}It's even got Mercedes sat-nav.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.56,0:10:15.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,不得不说\N{\fs90}And I've got to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.85,0:10:17.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,阿斯顿马丁和奔驰\N{\fs90}Aston Martin and Mercedes,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.56,0:10:20.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,是维多利亚女皇嫁给阿尔伯特后\N{\fs90}that is the best Anglo-German marriage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.98,0:10:23.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,最佳的英德联姻\N{\fs90}since Queen Victoria married Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.72,0:10:27.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是詹姆斯不同意\N{\fs90}James, though, disagreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.41,0:10:30.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,事实上 这才是最佳的英德联姻产物\N{\fs90}Actually, this is the best Anglo-German marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.96,0:10:38.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车是完美的\N{\fs90}It's perfect, in fact, because it has all the things
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.23,0:10:41.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,它具有标准英国车的所有优点\N{\fs90}that we like to think of as being Britishness in a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.23,0:10:44.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,感觉是由一位穿着围裙的男人所制造\N{\fs90}The sense that it was made by men in aprons,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.32,0:10:47.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,体现了其工匠技巧和使用的传统材料\N{\fs90}that there are craft skills and traditional materials involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.65,0:10:50.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且你还可以享受德国人的高科技\N{\fs90}But then you've got the Germans there, with their hi-tech
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.23,0:10:52.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,和他们的制造效率\N{\fs90}and their manufacturing efficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.85,0:10:56.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,绝对的经典之作\N{\fs90}It's absolutely wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.19,0:11:00.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,它很平和\N{\fs90}It's... It's very serene.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.38,0:11:03.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能说出它的不少参数\N{\fs90}There are a lot of numbers I could quote on this car.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:07.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,如最基本的 极速 马力 百公里加速\N{\fs90}You know, the usual: top speed, power, 0-60.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.05,0:11:07.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,之类的废话\N{\fs90}All that sort of irrelevant rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.98,0:11:12.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我不会 因为那太肤浅\N{\fs90}But I'm not going to, because that would be, frankly, uncouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.24,0:11:16.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,说到肤浅\N{\fs90}Oh, talking of uncouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.65,0:11:22.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,我承认 这不是台安静的车\N{\fs90}I'll admit, this is not a quiet car.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.43,0:11:31.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,它搭载了嗓门又沉又躁的\N{\fs90}You've got that big bass rumble and roar
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.45,0:11:34.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,6.2升 V8 HEMI发动机\N{\fs90}from the 6.2 litre V8 HEMI.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:38.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且 还附加尖锐狂躁的机增声浪\N{\fs90}And over the top, that shrill, manic whine of the supercharger.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.59,0:11:42.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,这两样都不太环保\N{\fs90}Neither is it a particularly economical one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.74,0:11:46.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,全油门状态下 84升的油箱\N{\fs90}At full chat, it'll chew through its 18.5-gallon fuel tank
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.90,0:11:48.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,13分钟就会用光\N{\fs90}in just 13 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.27,0:11:52.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且 它得吸入大量空气\N{\fs90}And, in fact, it needs so much air
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.92,0:11:55.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,来配合汽油消耗\N{\fs90}to mix with all that petrol it's drinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.07,0:11:56.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们不得不移除一个大灯\N{\fs90}they had to remove one of the headlights
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.07,0:11:59.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,换成强制进气口\N{\fs90}and replace it with a ram-air intake
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.18,0:12:01.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,给引擎供氧\N{\fs90}to feed air to the engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.12,0:12:03.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以他们把眼睛换成了鼻子\N{\fs90}So they swapped its eye for a nostril.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.69,0:12:10.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,好处是\N{\fs90}The upside of all this, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.63,0:12:13.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,它超快\N{\fs90}is that it's extremely fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.90,0:12:18.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,04比保时捷911 GT3还快\N{\fs90}It'll do the standing quarter faster than a Porsche 911 GT3,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.27,0:12:20.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,售价只要五万镑\N{\fs90}but it costs, what, £50,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.36,0:12:24.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯那劳斯莱斯可以买五台这车\N{\fs90}You could have five of these for one of James May's Rolls-Royces.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.01,0:12:27.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,又可以炸隧道了\N{\fs90}Oh, hello. This looks like a tunnel opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.14,0:12:32.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,消停点\N{\fs90}Stop doing that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.38,0:12:38.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德那车的声音实在是太糟糕了\N{\fs90}That is a genuinely horrible noise that Hammond's car's making,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.96,0:12:40.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,他就是停不下来\N{\fs90}and he just keeps doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.65,0:12:43.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,先猛踩一个踏板 再猛踩另一个\N{\fs90}He keeps stamping one pedal, then stamping the other one
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:45.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,就这么头脑简单\N{\fs90}in his binary style.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.67,0:12:54.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,可惜 引擎声不是那台车唯一的问题\N{\fs90}Sadly, the engine noise wasn't the only irritation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.90,0:12:59.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是意大利的加油站巡游么\N{\fs90}Is this just going to be a tour of Italy's petrol stations?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.41,0:13:01.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,这取决于它们之间的距离 不是么\N{\fs90}Well, it depends how far apart they are, doesn't it, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.84,0:13:04.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,换角度想 这也是吃小吃的良机\N{\fs90}Look at it this way, think of the snacking opportunities.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.58,0:13:06.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,你为美食而来意大利\N{\fs90}You've come to Italy for food.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.38,0:13:07.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,但不是为了吃薯条\N{\fs90}Yeah, but not crisps.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:10.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 不是为了薯条或可怕的美国香肠\N{\fs90}No, not crisps and hideous sausages from America.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.05,0:13:13.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,不一定 每个加油站的餐食都不一样\N{\fs90}You don't know. It'll be different in different petrol stations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.38,0:13:14.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不会的  -会的\N{\fs90}-It won't. -It will.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.65,0:13:16.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,有文艺复兴风格的加油站么\N{\fs90}Are there any Renaissance petrol stations we could visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.01,0:13:17.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者巴洛克式的\N{\fs90}Baroque?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.63,0:13:19.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有 也没有文艺复兴风格的香肠\N{\fs90}No. Nor are there any Renaissance sausage rolls in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.43,0:13:20.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的天老爷\N{\fs90}For God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.27,0:13:21.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,在喂饱了他车\N{\fs90}Having filled up his car,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.85,0:13:25.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,和他自己后 我们重新上路\N{\fs90}and himself, we were back on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.67,0:13:30.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,情况通报\N{\fs90}A quick situation update.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.52,0:13:32.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,我正驾车穿越阳光明媚的\N{\fs90}I'm driving through sunny It--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.03,0:13:34.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,闭嘴\N{\fs90}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.01,0:13:38.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,坏消息 詹姆斯 前面恐怕又有隧道\N{\fs90}Bad news, James. I'm afraid there's a tunnel coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.30,0:13:39.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,准备好了么\N{\fs90}Are you ready? Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.75,0:13:42.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,别来了 哈蒙德 放松享受安静吧\N{\fs90}Don't do it, Hammond. Just relax. Enjoy a bit of quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.42,0:13:47.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,别搞了\N{\fs90}Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.16,0:13:50.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,这有谁不爱呢\N{\fs90}You have got to love that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.59,0:13:56.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快 我们来到文艺复兴之城 佛罗伦萨\N{\fs90}Soon, we arrived in the Renaissance city of Florence,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.78,0:14:00.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,过去大壮游的必经之地\N{\fs90}a traditional stopping point on the Grand Tour of old.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.57,0:14:03.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,建筑物\N{\fs90}Architecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.71,0:14:07.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,佛罗伦萨歌剧院 我们为此而来\N{\fs90}Opera di Firenze. This is what we're here for.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.54,0:14:10.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们就是为它而来啊\N{\fs90}This is why we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.58,0:14:12.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,最棒的是\N{\fs90}Best of all, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.56,0:14:16.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯和我甩掉了哈蒙德\N{\fs90}James and I had managed to lose Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.28,0:14:19.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,他那道奇 真把你惹毛了是吧\N{\fs90}He's really offending you, isn't he, with his Dodge?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.18,0:14:22.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一般不这么说\N{\fs90}Honestly, I wouldn't say this lightly,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.41,0:14:25.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,我打从心底里\N{\fs90}but I have developed a genuine, deep,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.36,0:14:27.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,深深憎恶那玩意\N{\fs90}deep, heartfelt hatred for that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.87,0:14:32.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,我懂 你快要成粉红豹电影里的德雷福斯督查了\N{\fs90}I can tell. You're going to go like Inspector Dreyfus in the Pink Panther films soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.92,0:14:34.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 我都开始抽搐了\N{\fs90}You're not wrong. I've developed a twitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.76,0:14:37.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,每当他靠近 我就等着他那愚蠢的噪音\N{\fs90}When he comes near me and I'm waiting for that stupid noise it makes,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.90,0:14:39.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,眼睛也开始颤抖\N{\fs90}my eye starts quivering.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.52,0:14:41.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像你在读一本好书的时候\N{\fs90}It's like somebody constantly being sick on you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.72,0:14:43.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,有人一直在你身上呕吐\N{\fs90}while you're trying to read a nice book.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.72,0:14:48.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,分道扬镳之后\N{\fs90}As we were on our own,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.56,0:14:50.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,我和杰里米决定去\N{\fs90}Jeremy and I decided to head for
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.41,0:14:52.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,著名的乌菲齐美术馆\N{\fs90}the renowned Uffizi Gallery...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.52,0:14:55.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,欣赏其中珍宝的同时\N{\fs90}where we would enjoy a bit of peace and quiet
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.59,0:14:55.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,还可以享受平静与安详\N{\fs90}as we appreciated its treasures.\N{\fs90}欣赏其中珍宝的同时\N{\fs90}where we would enjoy a bit of peace and quiet
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.61,0:14:58.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,还可以享受平静与安详\N{\fs90}as we appreciated its treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.37,0:15:15.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,谁饿了 现在是甜甜圈时间\N{\fs90}Who's hungry? Cos it's doughnut time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.32,0:15:16.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,太好了\N{\fs90}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.81,0:15:19.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个给你了\N{\fs90}You can have that one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.75,0:15:21.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,快撒点糖粉\N{\fs90}Put sprinkles on that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.92,0:15:25.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,在意大利这随便什么山上浪起来吧\N{\fs90}Party on the hill in... wherever we are. Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.69,0:15:30.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,这地方终于有了点生气\N{\fs90}Finally bringing some life into this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.06,0:15:37.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德换上新轮胎后\N{\fs90}After Hammond had fitted some new tyres...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.80,0:15:43.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,我和詹姆斯决定放弃乌菲齐\N{\fs90}...James and I abandoned our visit to the Uffizi...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.74,0:15:46.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,把他赶出城去\N{\fs90}and escorted him out of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.67,0:15:49.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 我们在城市的另外一边\N{\fs90}Hammond, we could see the smoke from your tyres
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.65,0:15:51.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,都能看到你的胎烟\N{\fs90}from the other side of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.78,0:15:53.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\fs90}I know! I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.18,0:15:56.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,从未有人\N{\fs90}Nobody in history has ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.45,0:15:59.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,会开阿斯顿马丁烧胎\N{\fs90}ever doughnuted an Aston Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.32,0:16:01.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为车主们都上了年纪\N{\fs90}Yeah, they're not young buyers, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.23,0:16:05.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 因为他们优雅且有教养\N{\fs90}No, they're refined and cultured.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.99,0:16:10.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,我真羡慕你 哈蒙德 因为你在车里能看到我的阿斯顿马丁\N{\fs90}I envy you, Hammond, cos you get to look at my Aston Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.03,0:16:14.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,-但你这台车在视觉上有个大问题  -什么\N{\fs90}-Yeah, but there's a big problem with it visually. -What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.81,0:16:16.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,它是棕色的\N{\fs90}It's brown!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.40,0:16:20.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是日落橙\N{\fs90}Sunburst Orange is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.23,0:16:23.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米 我要担心吗 大家都听说过这俗语\N{\fs90}Jeremy, I shouldn't worry. We all know the expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.90,0:16:25.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,棕色的夜空 牧羊人的爱\N{\fs90}Brown sky at night, shepherd's delight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.95,0:16:29.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,那小伙就去偷东西 你知道么\N{\fs90}That bloke's been done for that theft, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.32,0:16:31.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,糊了一手棕色被抓现行\N{\fs90}They caught him brown-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.50,0:16:32.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,我开始幻想\N{\fs90}I'm starting to imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.94,0:16:37.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德没有脑袋或者皮肤的样子\N{\fs90}what Richard Hammond would look like without a head... or skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.59,0:16:41.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德损完马丁的颜色后\N{\fs90}Once Hammond had finished rubbishing the Aston's colour,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.45,0:16:44.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,他开始挑战其性能了\N{\fs90}he started to challenge its performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.72,0:16:50.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德现在在我后面 看来他想超车\N{\fs90}Hammond is driving along behind me now like he wants to get past.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.56,0:16:54.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,傻小子\N{\fs90}Stupid boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.96,0:16:58.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你那车的最高车速是多少\N{\fs90}What is the top speed of that car of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:01.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,320公里\N{\fs90}199 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.08,0:17:06.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,我这有322 所以离我远点\N{\fs90}Exactly. This will do 200, so back off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.92,0:17:09.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 但是你车贵了10万英镑\N{\fs90}Well, yes, but it's 100 grand more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.43,0:17:11.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,这两公里的提速真贵\N{\fs90}That's a very expensive mile an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.06,0:17:16.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,与其陷入无用的口水战\N{\fs90}Rather than get into a pointless war of words,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.67,0:17:19.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我决定将计就计\N{\fs90}I decided to put Hammond in his place
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.56,0:17:22.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,邀请停在这里\N{\fs90}and invited him to pull over here...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.14,0:17:25.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,穆杰罗赛道\N{\fs90}...at the Mugello race track.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.41,0:17:32.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么带我来这全无文化底蕴的地方\N{\fs90}Why have you brought me to this not-at-all cultural place?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.63,0:17:36.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我想给教教他什么才是真正的速度\N{\fs90}Because I want to teach him a lesson about what real speed is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.65,0:17:38.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,但他车有700多匹马力\N{\fs90}But he's got over 700 horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.98,0:17:40.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道 但你记得大钢牙吗\N{\fs90}Yes, I know, but you remember Jaws:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.63,0:17:42.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,戴着钢牙的大家伙\N{\fs90}big metal teeth, huge man?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.70,0:17:44.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯邦德轻松地从窗户把他丢了出去\N{\fs90}James Bond simply threw him through a window,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.78,0:17:46.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我就要这么教训他\N{\fs90}and that's what I'm gonna do to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.67,0:17:49.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不参加你介意么\N{\fs90}- Do you mind if I don't take part in this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.73,0:17:50.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,我来就行\N{\fs90}I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.54,0:17:58.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德又换了一套轮胎之后\N{\fs90}So, as Hammond had some new tyres fitted... again,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.93,0:18:02.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,我先下赛道熟悉下情况\N{\fs90}I took to the track for some sighting laps.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.90,0:18:09.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,首先必须说明\N{\fs90}Now, let's get one thing straight from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.70,0:18:15.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,阿斯顿马丁并不是为了跑圈而设计的\N{\fs90}Aston Martins are not really designed to do track work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.26,0:18:19.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们只要好看 就够了\N{\fs90}They're designed to look good, and that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.99,0:18:22.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,这台DB11的底盘\N{\fs90}Yes, the chassis on this, the DB11,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.93,0:18:26.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,是由一名前莲花工程师研发的\N{\fs90}was developed by a former Lotus engineer,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.23,0:18:27.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,厂家明确告诉他\N{\fs90}but they actually told him
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.54,0:18:31.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,调校时要更注重舒适性 而非操控性\N{\fs90}to tune it more for comfort than handling.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.67,0:18:34.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,话虽如此\N{\fs90}That being said,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.11,0:18:40.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,但它仍有铝制底盘和空气动力魔法\N{\fs90}this has an aluminium chassis and some aero trickery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.87,0:18:44.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,后窗的缝隙能导入气流\N{\fs90}Air is sucked into holes behind the rear windows
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.50,0:18:48.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后从后备箱盖上的通风口导出\N{\fs90}and then shot out of a vent on the boot lid,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.03,0:18:51.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,充当了尾翼的角色\N{\fs90}giving me a sort of air rear wing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.38,0:18:57.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,给我抓地力 大量抓地力\N{\fs90}Giving me grip... a lot of grip.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.40,0:19:01.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车的牵引力控制系统太惊艳了\N{\fs90}And the traction control is simply astonishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.74,0:19:04.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,大部分车上 那就像有人用锤子在砸你的头\N{\fs90}In most cars, it's like somebody hitting you on the head with a hammer,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.78,0:19:06.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,但在这 就是\N{\fs90}but in this, it's just going,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.38,0:19:10.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,等下等下等下 搞定\N{\fs90}"Erm... Hang on, hang on, hang on." There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.15,0:19:14.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,天地良心 这车真不错\N{\fs90}Bloody hellfire! This is very, very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.38,0:19:20.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,至少碾压哈蒙德那台傻道奇\N{\fs90}Certainly it's good enough to be able to totally destroy
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.79,0:19:23.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,是绰绰有余了\N{\fs90}Hammond's idiotic Dodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.79,0:19:29.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车没有镁制车顶\N{\fs90}This does not have a magnesium roof,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.94,0:19:31.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,或碳纤维传动轴\N{\fs90}carbon-fibre prop shaft.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.18,0:19:33.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,发动机不是铝的 而是铸铁\N{\fs90}The engine isn't made from aluminium, it's made from cast iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.01,0:19:37.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,你能感觉到 要条件允许 他们会用石头来造\N{\fs90}And you get the impression they'd have made it from stone if they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.14,0:19:42.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,它有的 是充足的动力储备\N{\fs90}What it does have is vast reserves of power,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.11,0:19:45.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,和更充足的个性\N{\fs90}and even vaster reserves of character.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.05,0:19:47.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车太欢快了\N{\fs90}This thing is just hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.99,0:19:56.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看他 还有那台棕色的小阿斯顿\N{\fs90}Look at him in his little brown Aston,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.32,0:19:59.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,一切尽在掌握 却毫无乐趣\N{\fs90}being all in control, and just not having fun, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.41,0:20:00.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,又有什么意义呢\N{\fs90}I mean, what's the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.11,0:20:05.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,瞎炫耀 还以为我做不到\N{\fs90}Showboating. Probably thinks I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.46,0:20:08.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,不好意思 哈蒙德 这可是一台600马力\N{\fs90}Well, I'm sorry, Hammond, this is a 600 horsepower,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.67,0:20:10.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,后轮驱动的阿斯顿马丁\N{\fs90}rear-wheel drive Aston Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.56,0:20:14.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我关掉了牵引力控制系统\N{\fs90}So I turned the traction control off,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.34,0:20:16.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,释放出了它的本性\N{\fs90}and all hell broke loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.56,0:20:33.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要像这样漂一整天\N{\fs90}It will do this all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.83,0:20:38.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,与此同时\N{\fs90}Meanwhile...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.07,0:20:42.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,大壮游原本的初衷之一\N{\fs90}One of the purposes of the original Grand Tour
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.42,0:20:44.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,不仅仅是欣赏和学习\N{\fs90}wasn't just to look at things and learn about things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.12,0:20:46.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,更是挖掘你的能力\N{\fs90}It was also to enhance your capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.04,0:20:50.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,你可以去学一些东西\N{\fs90}You would learn to do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.54,0:20:52.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,比如写十四行诗\N{\fs90}You might do... I don't know, writing sonnets,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.18,0:20:55.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,演奏乐器 做点地方菜肴之类的\N{\fs90}playing musical instruments, regional cooking, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.06,0:20:57.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我要来尝试一下水彩画\N{\fs90}I'm having a go at watercolour painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.71,0:20:59.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的能让人心情愉悦\N{\fs90}It's absolutely delightful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.91,0:21:03.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,除了我的思绪偶尔会被哈蒙德那辆\N{\fs90}Apart from my reverie is occasionally interrupted
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.34,0:21:06.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,肌肉车发出的令人厌恶的轰鸣声打断\N{\fs90}by the... disgusting bellow of Hammond's muscle car.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.83,0:21:11.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德同志找来了一辆直升机\N{\fs90}Mr. Hammond appears to have organised a helicopter
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.86,0:21:13.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,记录下这场表演\N{\fs90}to record the event.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.48,0:21:19.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈哈 克拉克森 超过我呀\N{\fs90}Ha-ha, Clarkson! Get past me now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.37,0:21:21.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,给你点烟色瞧瞧\N{\fs90}Smokescreen you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.35,0:21:28.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,你简直蠢到家了 哈蒙德\N{\fs90}What a moron you are, Hammond!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.44,0:21:31.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,给我闪开\N{\fs90}Get out of my way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.96,0:21:36.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不是一项很有文化的行为\N{\fs90}This is not a particularly cultural thing to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.71,0:21:39.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这很好玩啊\N{\fs90}but it is very good fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.62,0:21:50.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,尽管哈蒙德和我一直在制造烟雾\N{\fs90}Even though Hammond and I were having a big smoky riot,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.83,0:21:52.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,但却什么也没学到\N{\fs90}we'd learned nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.47,0:21:55.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们决定要科学一点\N{\fs90}So we decided to get scientific
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.91,0:21:59.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,认真做一个计时圈\N{\fs90}and do a proper timed flying lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.32,0:22:12.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,这很重要\N{\fs90}This matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.53,0:22:15.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了英国 也为了欧洲\N{\fs90}This is for Britain. This is for Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.70,0:22:17.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,不要做蠢事\N{\fs90}No silly business.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.54,0:22:20.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,以最快速度跑完这一圈\N{\fs90}Let's just get round this as fast as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.44,0:22:28.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,当计时圈完成了之后\N{\fs90}With the flying lap completed,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.45,0:22:31.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们碰头来比较圈速\N{\fs90}we met to compare times.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.84,0:22:34.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,-来吧 你先说 -好吧 2分\N{\fs90}-Go on, then. -All right, then. Two...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.86,0:22:36.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我也是 -好的\N{\fs90}-Yes. -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.48,0:22:38.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,18秒\N{\fs90}18 seconds...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.99,0:22:41.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,-18 -对啊 怎么了 你是多少秒\N{\fs90}-18? -Yes. Why, what have you got? What are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.83,0:22:44.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,我也是18 但是\N{\fs90}18. B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.27,0:22:48.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你确定不是编出来的吗 -不是 2分18秒\N{\fs90}-You're not making that up? -No. Two minutes 18...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.23,0:22:49.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗬\N{\fs90}Ooh!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.32,0:22:51.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,79\N{\fs90}...point 79.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.27,0:22:52.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,感谢上帝\N{\fs90}Oh, thank God for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.63,0:22:55.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,绝对优势 我是35\N{\fs90}I'm... It's crushing. Three-five.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.85,0:22:57.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么 这哪叫绝对优势啊\N{\fs90}Well, it's hardly crushing, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.36,0:23:00.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是因为 -我不明白为什么你要接受这个挑战\N{\fs90}-No, cos that's... -I don't know why you accepted the challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.57,0:23:04.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,你多花十万才快了不到半秒\N{\fs90}It's less then half a second for your extra 100 grand.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.88,0:23:07.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,别幸灾乐祸了\N{\fs90}Well, hardly a big gloat, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.56,0:23:12.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,十万英镑只换来了半秒\N{\fs90}It's ￡100,000 for half a second
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.44,0:23:14.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,和1.6公里的最高时速\N{\fs90}and 1mph top speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.17,0:23:18.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们的最大成就就是保持独立240年而已了\N{\fs90}240 years of independence and that's the best they can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.24,0:23:22.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,当哈蒙德用烧胎让自己高兴起来\N{\fs90}As Hammond cheered himself up with some doughnuts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.43,0:23:26.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后又换了一组轮胎的时候\N{\fs90}...and then another set of tyres...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.35,0:23:30.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,我去找詹姆斯了\N{\fs90}...I went to join James.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.57,0:23:36.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,见鬼\N{\fs90}Oh, shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.41,0:23:50.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,-顺便 你赢了吗 -当然\N{\fs90}-Did you beat him, by the way? -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.16,0:23:51.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,好样的\N{\fs90}Good man.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.63,0:23:57.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,当太阳躲入托斯卡纳山背后\N{\fs90}As the sun slipped behind the Tuscan hills,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.82,0:24:01.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们也愉快地画了一个多小时\N{\fs90}we spent an enjoyable hour or so painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.10,0:24:03.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,可惜好景不长\N{\fs90}But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.62,0:24:12.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们在干吗\N{\fs90}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.79,0:24:14.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我正在拆弹 哈蒙德\N{\fs90}I'm defusing a bomb, Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.61,0:24:15.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,你觉得我还能在干吗\N{\fs90}What do you think I'm doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.69,0:24:17.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在烤蛋糕\N{\fs90}I'm baking a cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.17,0:24:19.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你们好像在画画 -我们就是在画画\N{\fs90}-It looks like you're painting. -We are painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.85,0:24:23.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后哈蒙德决定也要试一试\N{\fs90}Hammond then decided he'd like to have a go as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.63,0:24:32.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,好嘞\N{\fs90}- Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.10,0:24:34.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,这样\N{\fs90}That one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.09,0:24:44.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快 我们艺术创作完成了\N{\fs90}Soon, our art was finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.48,0:24:48.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得我画的太快了\N{\fs90}I think I've rushed mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.59,0:24:51.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这还不算什么\N{\fs90}Still, could be worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.24,0:24:55.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,在此之前 我以为\N{\fs90}It was difficult, before I saw this,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.13,0:24:58.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,想象出一个比真车更难看的东西很难\N{\fs90}to imagine anything more hideous than the actual car.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.71,0:25:00.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,但你做到了 哈蒙德\N{\fs90}But you've done it, Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.72,0:25:05.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,你就是为了把这张纸画满吧\N{\fs90}It's the way that you've managed to eradicate any sense of place.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.36,0:25:06.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 我知道\N{\fs90}Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.60,0:25:14.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,你在抽搐 他在抽搐\N{\fs90}Your twitch! He's twitching!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.25,0:25:16.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,即使在看你这辆车的画\N{\fs90}Even when he looks at the picture of your car,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.83,0:25:19.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,他也会不由自主的抽搐\N{\fs90}he's actually twitching!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.92,0:25:24.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,所有的努力\N{\fs90}All of the work...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.69,0:25:27.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,劳斯莱斯在曜影上的所有努力\N{\fs90}All of the work that Rolls-Royce put into that Dawn
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.80,0:25:31.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,让它变得安静 文雅 高尚\N{\fs90}to make it quiet and refined and sublime,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.71,0:25:33.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,以及你的所有期望\N{\fs90}and all those things you'd expect,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.45,0:25:35.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,在你的道奇旁边都变得毫无意义\N{\fs90}it all counts for absolutely nothing if it's anywhere near your Dodge,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.46,0:25:37.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你只能听到它的噪音\N{\fs90}because that's all you can hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.76,0:25:39.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,我还要再说两句那辆地狱猫\N{\fs90}Do you know something about that Hellcat?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.83,0:25:41.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,是这样 我做了一些调查\N{\fs90}OK, I've done some research into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.87,0:25:45.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,地狱猫参照的是老款克莱斯勒300C\N{\fs90}The Hellcat is based on the old Chrysler 300C.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.03,0:25:46.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,本质上是同一辆车\N{\fs90}Underneath, it's the same car.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.58,0:25:51.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,而300C的原型是90年代的奔驰E级\N{\fs90}And the 300C, underneath, is a 1990s Mercedes E-Class.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.86,0:25:53.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以道奇做的就是\N{\fs90}So what Dodge has done with that thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.62,0:25:58.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,把700马力放进一辆20年前的出租车里\N{\fs90}if they put 700 horsepower in a 20-year-old taxi...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.36,0:25:59.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这样的\N{\fs90}that's what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.55,0:26:00.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管怎样\N{\fs90}Anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.81,0:26:03.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你们想听两个老男人\N{\fs90}if you want to listen to two old men
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.76,0:26:08.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我玩耍的时候滔滔不绝地说着音乐和歌剧\N{\fs90}dribble on about music and opera whilst I have fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.25,0:26:10.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,接下来你们将看到更多\N{\fs90}there'll be more of that later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.27,0:26:12.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,而现在是时候看一眼后视镜\N{\fs90}But now it's time for us to check our mirrors
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.92,0:26:16.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后左转进入唠嗑街了\N{\fs90}and make a smooth left into Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.18,0:26:25.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fs90}It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.11,0:26:27.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不得不说\N{\fs90}Now... I have to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.80,0:26:32.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯对惠特比之行很是期待\N{\fs90}James was very, very excited about coming to Whitby,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.76,0:26:35.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为他听说这里是英国的喷气飞机中心\N{\fs90}because he'd heard that it's the centre of the British jet industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.50,0:26:36.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,他期盼着能够花几天的时间\N{\fs90}He was very much looking forward to spending
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.94,0:26:39.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看协和的旧设计图\N{\fs90}a couple of days looking at old drawings of Concord,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.46,0:26:40.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,但随后他发现\N{\fs90}but then he discovered that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.47,0:26:43.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,所谓的惠特比喷气机其实是这个\N{\fs90}Whitby jet is actually this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.10,0:26:45.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,看上去像是一块煤\N{\fs90}It looks like coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.73,0:26:47.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,-就是煤 -真的吗\N{\fs90}-It is coal. -Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.06,0:26:48.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,是这样的 他们发现\N{\fs90}Thing is, though, they've worked out...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.90,0:26:50.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,显然你不能再烧煤了\N{\fs90}Obviouasly, you can't burn coal any more
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.24,0:26:51.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为阿尔 戈尔疯了\N{\fs90}because Al Gore goes nuts
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.68,0:26:53.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,一只北极熊摔了一跤\N{\fs90}and a polar bear falls over,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.61,0:26:55.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以他们打磨了下它\N{\fs90}so they polish it up
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.20,0:26:57.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且说它很珍贵\N{\fs90}and then say it's precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.37,0:27:00.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,有意思 我这里有一份从惠特比\N{\fs90}That's interesting, this, cos I've got the blurb here
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.27,0:27:03.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,最老的零售商那里拿的简介 上面说\N{\fs90}from Whitby's oldest retailer of the stuff, and it says,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.82,0:27:06.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,不同于其他宝石\N{\fs90}"Unlike other gemstones,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.55,0:27:10.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,黑玉实际上是一种化石木\N{\fs90}jet is actually fossilised wood."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.22,0:27:12.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 因为不同于其他宝石\N{\fs90}Yes, because unlike other gemstones,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.01,0:27:13.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,它是块煤\N{\fs90}it's coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.82,0:27:15.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道 但是\N{\fs90}Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.40,0:27:17.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,-但它 -这就是煤 对吧\N{\fs90}-But it's... -It's coal, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.12,0:27:19.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,不同于其他宝石 哈蒙德 它还便宜的多\N{\fs90}Unlike other gemstones, Hammond, it's a lot cheaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.54,0:27:22.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的吗 它确实应该便宜\N{\fs90}Well, yes, it would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.21,0:27:25.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,正经点 看 你可以花32英镑买到一枚黑玉戒指\N{\fs90}Well, seriously, you can get a jet ring, look, for 32 quid.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.28,0:27:28.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,10镑就能买一堆了 它是煤啊\N{\fs90}You get a sack of it for ten quid. It's coal!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.16,0:27:29.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,是这样的\N{\fs90}Thing is, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.26,0:27:30.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们想过这件事\N{\fs90}We were thinking the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.64,0:27:33.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在的汽车厂商会用竹子 白蜡树 胡桃木\N{\fs90}you know carmakers now they use bamboo, ash, walnut
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.77,0:27:35.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有碳纤维去装饰车子\N{\fs90}and carbon fibre to decorate bits of a car?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.99,0:27:38.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他们为什么不用黑玉呢 -没错\N{\fs90}-Why don't they use jet? -Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.45,0:27:40.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,大家都希望车里能有点黑玉\N{\fs90}Anybody would like to have some jet in their car.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.74,0:27:43.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,实际上我们做了个实验 哈蒙德\N{\fs90}Actually, we've been doing a little bit of experimenting, Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.30,0:27:47.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,我做了一个样品 这是用黑玉做档头的变速杆\N{\fs90}I've made a prototype. This is a gearstick with a jet knob...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.40,0:27:50.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的很棒\N{\fs90}...on the top. It's brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.49,0:27:52.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我还没给它抛光 但是当你换挡的时候\N{\fs90}I mean, it's not polished yet, but you change gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.98,0:27:55.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,它会把你的手弄脏\N{\fs90}It does make your hand a bit dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.08,0:27:57.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,话虽如此 但它是个很好用的提示器\N{\fs90}But, no, that's a handy reminder. It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.32,0:27:58.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 你说的完全正确\N{\fs90}Exactly. No, you're absolutely right 'cause you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.35,0:28:01.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,有时候当你开着一辆不熟悉的车在高速公路上\N{\fs90}sometimes you drive an unfamiliar car, you're on the motorway
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.79,0:28:03.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,你会想 我挂到六档了吗\N{\fs90}and you think, "Oh, did I change into sixth?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.69,0:28:05.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 挂了\N{\fs90}Yeah, I did."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.30,0:28:09.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,有一些话我想在唠嗑街里说\N{\fs90}Here's some conversation... for Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.32,0:28:12.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,有个坏消息 我们的国家正面临一个问题\N{\fs90}Erm... Bad news. There is a problem right now in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.43,0:28:15.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,学习驾驶的人不够多\N{\fs90}Not enough people are learning to drive. Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.17,0:28:20.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,在2007年 有超过16000场驾驶考试\N{\fs90}In 2007, just over 16,000 driving tests were conducted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.56,0:28:24.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,但去年这个数字跌到了4650\N{\fs90}Last year, that had dropped to 4,650.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.73,0:28:26.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是事实 在不到十年的时间里\N{\fs90}That is a true fact. In less than ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.87,0:28:28.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,从16000下降到了4000\N{\fs90}16,000 down to 4,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.94,0:28:30.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道为什么会这样\N{\fs90}And I know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.05,0:28:31.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为现在这些刚进入社会的孩子们\N{\fs90}It's because kids leave school these days,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.77,0:28:33.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们不知道希特勒是谁\N{\fs90}they've no idea who Hitler was,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.32,0:28:34.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们不会算数\N{\fs90}they can't add up.
