Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.95,0:39:52.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错 -嗯\N{\fs90}-Yeah, exactly. -Erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.82,0:39:55.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,当哈蒙德奋力将画放进车里\N{\fs90}While Hammond struggled to get the painting in his car
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.76,0:39:57.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,踏上漫漫回英路时\N{\fs90}for the long trip back to England...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.69,0:39:59.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\fs90}Er...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.39,0:40:04.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯和我独自开向了意大利的荣耀\N{\fs90}...James and I set off alone into the glory that is Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.73,0:40:12.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,难以形容 看这景色呀\N{\fs90}Oh, my word. Look at that view.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.11,0:40:16.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的天呐\N{\fs90}Holy moley!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.95,0:40:28.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,当晚在维罗纳\N{\fs90}That evening in Verona,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.63,0:40:31.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在米其林餐厅里美餐\N{\fs90}we dined well at a Michelin-starred restaurant,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.82,0:40:35.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后我们去看了一个叫 卡门 的东西\N{\fs90}and then we went to see something called Carmen,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.08,0:40:38.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,但那和我们期待的东西完全不一样\N{\fs90}which wasn't at all what we were expecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.71,0:40:54.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,他没回家对吧\N{\fs90}He hasn't gone home, has he?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.66,0:41:07.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,第二天早上天一亮我们就起了\N{\fs90}The next morning, we were up at first light
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.36,0:41:09.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,想要再次逃脱\N{\fs90}to attempt another escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.80,0:41:14.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 他的房间在这里\N{\fs90}James... that's his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.24,0:41:25.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车有悄声启动功能 但我不会用\N{\fs90}This has a quiet-start facility on it, but I don't know how it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.15,0:41:27.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,摁它\N{\fs90}Push it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.68,0:41:30.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,我可以这车很安静\N{\fs90}I could... It's really quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.50,0:41:32.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,你启动吧 你没问题\N{\fs90}You start... You'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.43,0:41:36.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,别吵\N{\fs90}Don't bong!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.69,0:41:40.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,很神奇不是么\N{\fs90}That's amazing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.73,0:41:44.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,大概每秒点火80次\N{\fs90}That's firing 80 times a second, roughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.36,0:41:46.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,啊没有噪音\N{\fs90}Ah, no noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.47,0:41:48.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,我可以就这样开出去\N{\fs90}I can just drive out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.44,0:41:51.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦你们好 车出问题啦\N{\fs90}Oh, hello! Car trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.74,0:41:54.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,-对啊-典型阿斯顿你瞧\N{\fs90}- Yeah.- Typical Aston, you see!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.17,0:41:55.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,这抛锚了\N{\fs90}It's broken down.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.38,0:41:56.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,你得抓紧时间了\N{\fs90}You haven't got long to get it going
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.61,0:41:59.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我眨眼就换好衣服 然后出发\N{\fs90}cos I'll be down again in a second, changed and ready to roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.59,0:42:00.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗨呀\N{\fs90}Ya-ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.08,0:42:10.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,当哈蒙德上去 风干他一身汗的时候\N{\fs90}Whilst Hammond was upstairs, chiselling off his sweat...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.46,0:42:14.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯和我开始跑路\N{\fs90}...James and I made a run for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.67,0:42:17.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,同时 防止他在高速上追到我们\N{\fs90}And, in case he caught up with us on the motorway,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.46,0:42:19.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们便采取了预防措施\N{\fs90}we took some precautions.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.40,0:42:25.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是天才之作\N{\fs90}This is the work of a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.61,0:42:28.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们现在从哈蒙德先生眼前消失无踪了\N{\fs90}We are now protected from Mr Hammond completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.68,0:42:38.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯的脑袋有点影响大局 不过也有办法\N{\fs90}James's head was a bit of a problem with this plan, but we've solved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.25,0:42:45.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,观众们 如果没认出来不要惊慌 是我\N{\fs90}Don't worry if you don't recognise me, viewers. It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.69,0:42:49.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,问题是 哈蒙德认得出来吗\N{\fs90}The question was, would Richard Hammond recognise him?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.86,0:42:52.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,理查德哈蒙德来了 我只要目视前方\N{\fs90}Here comes Richard Hammond. Just look straight ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.53,0:42:54.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,目视前方\N{\fs90}Look straight ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.20,0:42:56.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,真相是\N{\fs90}And the answer was...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.25,0:42:57.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,不能看\N{\fs90}Not looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.42,0:43:02.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,妈蛋 他正朝我招手呢\N{\fs90}Oh, God. He's waving at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.32,0:43:08.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,那他就算是发现我们了是吧\N{\fs90}Well, he's clocked us, hasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.34,0:43:09.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得那车就是被飞石打了\N{\fs90}I think you're better off getting stone chips than looking like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.96,0:43:11.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,也比他包成那样好看\N{\fs90}than looking like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.89,0:43:15.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,救命 救命 我快包不住了\N{\fs90}Mayday. Mayday. I'm disintegrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.28,0:43:19.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,就在詹姆斯撕掉他自己的包装纸\N{\fs90}Whilst James unwrapped himself
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.36,0:43:22.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,理查德穿过被毁的肖像画加油的时候\N{\fs90}and Richard filled up through his ruined present,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.36,0:43:25.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,我突然灵机一动\N{\fs90}I had another brainwave.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.52,0:43:28.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我打算把他引到维琴察的市中心去\N{\fs90}I'm gonna lead him into the centre of Vicenza, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.25,0:43:29.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\fs90}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.78,0:43:32.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,我刚发了个推 然后也转到了Facebook上\N{\fs90}I've sent out a tweet, and I put this on Facebook,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.16,0:43:35.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,告诉大家理查德哈蒙德会现身市中心广场\N{\fs90}saying that Richard Hammond will be appearing in the main square, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.22,0:43:38.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,啊 所以到时候他一出现\N{\fs90}-Yes. -So he gets out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.26,0:43:39.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,他就会被围住 没错\N{\fs90}-He's mobbed. -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.70,0:43:41.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们趁机溜走  -很好 \N{\fs90}-We scarper -Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.36,0:43:42.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,-明白吗 -我喜欢\N{\fs90}-OK? -I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.77,0:43:44.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,你是用意大利语发的吗 是\N{\fs90}-Have you done it in Italian? -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.57,0:43:45.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,那就好 \N{\fs90}Oh, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.49,0:43:47.47,字幕,,0,0,0,, 唯一不妥的 我犯了个小错误\N{\fs90}Only thing is, I've made a slight mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.49,0:43:49.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,我这上边写的是理查德哈蒙德会\N{\fs90}I have said here that Richard Hammond will be -
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.51,0:43:51.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,我本来想说 现身 \N{\fs90}I wanted to say "appearing" but I've put
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.25,0:43:53.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,结果打成了 献身\N{\fs90}  "exhibiting himself".
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.71,0:43:55.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,这样更能吸引人啊\N{\fs90}Well, it'll get a crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.27,0:44:04.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,上路后 我就开始了计划的实施\N{\fs90}Back on the move, I put my plan into action.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.35,0:44:07.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 我们要不从这下高速吧\N{\fs90}I thought we'd turn off the motorway here, Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.82,0:44:10.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,维琴察有个专门烧胎画圈的地方\N{\fs90}Vicenza's gota doughnuting area in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.97,0:44:12.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,是吗\N{\fs90}Has it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.19,0:44:13.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 那里没有古建筑\N{\fs90}Yeah, no old statues.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.70,0:44:18.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,有的只是星巴克 麦当劳 和唐恩甜甜圈\N{\fs90}There's Starbucks,McDonald's, Dunkin' Donuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.21,0:44:20.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说的没错吧 詹姆斯\N{\fs90}I'm right, aren't I, James?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.22,0:44:22.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,我记得维琴察他们有支橄榄球队来着\N{\fs90}I think they've got an American football team
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.29,0:44:23.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,是吧\N{\fs90}haven't they, in Vicenza?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.74,0:44:26.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 维琴察红熊队\N{\fs90}They have, the Vicenza Red Bears.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.65,0:44:28.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,好\N{\fs90}OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.51,0:44:30.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们就去看看\N{\fs90}We'll have a little mooch about.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.34,0:44:35.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快 我们就离市中心不远了\N{\fs90}Soon, we were approaching the centre of the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.45,0:44:38.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,只要那群人能够\N{\fs90}I just need a crowd big enough
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.88,0:44:42.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,缠住他20分钟 我就够了\N{\fs90}to keep him occupied for 20 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.51,0:44:45.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不知道能有多少人看到我发的推\N{\fs90}I don't know how many people will have read my tweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.26,0:44:47.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,估计也就几百吧\N{\fs90}A couple of hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.53,0:44:51.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,和我估计的差的不多\N{\fs90}I was nearly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.96,0:44:56.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的天\N{\fs90}Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.85,0:45:04.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,我错了\N{\fs90}This has gone really wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.48,0:45:10.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,这回真玩大了 杰里米\N{\fs90}-This has gone so spectacularly wrong. -Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.29,0:45:18.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,我滴妈\N{\fs90}Oh, my word!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.96,0:45:21.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们好 这是有什么活动吗\N{\fs90}Hello. Is there an event on?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.80,0:45:26.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,你要找的是哈蒙德\N{\fs90}It's Mr Hammond you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.75,0:45:30.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德开的是那辆道奇\N{\fs90}Mr Hammond is in the Dodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.66,0:45:35.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 这有点吓人呦\N{\fs90}Oh, this is unnerving.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.68,0:45:37.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,这一直都这么热闹吗 \N{\fs90}Is it always this busy here?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.49,0:45:39.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,还是今天有什么事啊\N{\fs90} What's going on today?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.19,0:45:44.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,快看 我们出来了\N{\fs90}Look at that, we're free
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.54,0:45:47.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,而哈蒙德还在里面困着\N{\fs90} and Hammond is stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.11,0:45:51.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,太棒了\N{\fs90}Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.49,0:45:52.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们出来啦\N{\fs90}We're out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.81,0:45:54.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德完喽\N{\fs90}Hammond is doomed!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.99,0:45:56.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,他完蛋喽\N{\fs90}He's doomed!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.63,0:45:59.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,当哈蒙德还以为\N{\fs90}Leaving Hammond in what he thought
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.80,0:46:02.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,他到了意大利的肌肉车圣地的时候\N{\fs90}was the muscle-car capital of Italy...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.27,0:46:05.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们喜欢听飙高转\N{\fs90}They like a rev.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.39,0:46:07.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们还真好这一口\N{\fs90}They do like a rev here.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.28,0:46:10.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,我和詹姆斯已经出城了\N{\fs90}...James and I headed out of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.68,0:46:14.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 离威尼斯只有37公里了\N{\fs90}Right, good. Venice, 23 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.48,0:46:20.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,凭心而论\N{\fs90}I think it's fair to say
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.86,0:46:25.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,这趟旅程确实是惨不忍睹\N{\fs90}that this entire trip has been a total disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.52,0:46:29.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这辆阿斯顿马丁却表现十分惊艳\N{\fs90}But the Aston Martin has been the complete opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.82,0:46:35.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,在赛道上 它比我想得要好太多太多\N{\fs90}It was much, much better than I thought it was going to be on the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.56,0:46:38.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,在公路上 它又是难以置信的安静和舒适\N{\fs90}It's staggeringly civilised and quiet on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.83,0:46:42.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,它真心是辆顶级的GT车\N{\fs90}It really is a superb grand tourer,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.16,0:46:44.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且还漂亮的要命\N{\fs90}and it is achingly pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.64,0:46:49.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,尤其是这身橙色的车漆\N{\fs90}Especially with this beautiful orange paintwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.78,0:46:54.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,或许杰里米或许已经对他的棕色阿斯顿暗生情愫\N{\fs90}Jeremy may have been won over by his brown Aston,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.57,0:46:58.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我则是完全迷上了我的劳斯莱斯\N{\fs90}but I was truly smitten with the Rolls-Royce.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.76,0:47:00.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,一台劳斯莱斯究竟意味着什么\N{\fs90}What is it about a Rolls-Royce?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.97,0:47:05.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,许多人都说这不是一辆爱车之人会喜欢的车\N{\fs90}A lot of people would say this isn't a car-lover's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.05,0:47:07.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,不运动 没活力\N{\fs90}It's not sporty, it's not dynamic,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.45,0:47:09.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有模式选择\N{\fs90}it doesn't have modes for you to set.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.09,0:47:10.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,连想换档都不行\N{\fs90}You can't even change the gears.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.38,0:47:13.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,你只能选择是前进还是倒车\N{\fs90}You can only put it in forward or reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.34,0:47:17.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,可我恰好觉得爱车之人一定会喜欢它\N{\fs90}And yet, I think this is a car for people who love cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.79,0:47:21.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它能带给你一种完全不同的驾驶体验\N{\fs90}because it gives you an entirely different driving experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.17,0:47:24.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,世界上没有那辆车能够像劳斯莱斯一样\N{\fs90}There is no other car that's quite like a Rolls-Royce,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.18,0:47:27.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,这么溺爱般的保护着你\N{\fs90}no other car that cossets you in the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.05,0:47:29.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一辆会对你好的车\N{\fs90}This is a car that is kind to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.80,0:47:34.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得你开着这辆车就不可能会生气\N{\fs90}I think it is actually impossible to be unhappy if you're driving this car.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.34,0:47:36.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看看我都经历些什么\N{\fs90}And look at what I've had to put up with
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.01,0:47:37.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,理查德哈蒙德 理查德哈蒙德\N{\fs90}Richard Hammond and Richard Hammond
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.84,0:47:39.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有理查德哈蒙德 道奇地狱猫\N{\fs90}Richard Hammond, the Dodge Hellcat
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.41,0:47:41.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,以及理查德哈蒙德 和道奇地狱猫 \N{\fs90}Richard Hammond, the Dodge Hellcat
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.14,0:47:43.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我依然很开心\N{\fs90}and I'm still happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.55,0:47:49.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,到达威尼斯的时候 我们心情大好\N{\fs90}As we arrived in Venice, we were in good spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.81,0:47:52.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,第二天早上\N{\fs90}And, the next morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.21,0:47:53.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们做了前人们\N{\fs90}we did what all our predecessors
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.98,0:47:56.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这大壮游时都会做的事\N{\fs90}on the Grand Tour would have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.59,0:47:59.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在水上享受了当地的美景\N{\fs90}We took in the sights from the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.56,0:48:04.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有哈蒙德的日子太爽了\N{\fs90}It's so nice without Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.24,0:48:06.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,昨天晚饭\N{\fs90}Dinner last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.83,0:48:08.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,点餐的时候没人在旁边说 \N{\fs90}Nice to order food without somebody going
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.78,0:48:10.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们有薯片吗 的感觉太好了\N{\fs90}Have you got any chips?"
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.39,0:48:13.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 还有 番茄酱在哪\N{\fs90}Yeah. "Where's the ketchup?"
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.63,0:48:16.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,他这辈子都不可能从那个广场出来了 \N{\fs90}He is never, ever going to get out of that square.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.03,0:48:16.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辈子\N{\fs90} I mean never.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.90,0:48:19.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,我估计他已经被踩死了或者被扯碎了\N{\fs90}I assume he's been crushed to death by now, or torn apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.91,0:48:23.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,看见了吗\N{\fs90}Have you seen that?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.33,0:48:25.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯 真有病\N{\fs90}-Yeah. -What a moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.32,0:48:28.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,一艘不合时宜的棕色汽艇\N{\fs90}An inappropriate brown powerboat.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.61,0:48:29.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,橙色\N{\fs90}Orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.92,0:48:32.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,这东西让开吗这 我还挺吃惊的\N{\fs90}Is that allowed round here? I'm surprised, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.25,0:48:35.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,伙计们\N{\fs90}Lads!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.06,0:48:37.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,真是粗野\N{\fs90}What a yob.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.20,0:48:39.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,我以为他的地狱猫就够糟了\N{\fs90}I thought his Hellcat was bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.89,0:48:42.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 住手\N{\fs90}Hammond, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.29,0:48:46.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,你这样真不合适 哈蒙德 别这样\N{\fs90}That's really inappropriate, Hammond. Don't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.34,0:48:48.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,这船非常容易晃 别\N{\fs90}This is very wobbly.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.70,0:48:50.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,别 别 哈蒙德\N{\fs90}Don't... Don't do that, Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.19,0:48:54.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,有谁饿了吗 谁想吃甜甜圈\N{\fs90}Who's hungry? Who's for doughnuts?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.20,0:48:55.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 停下\N{\fs90}Hammond, stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.61,0:49:00.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,水上甜甜圈\N{\fs90}Yah! Water doughnut!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.45,0:49:02.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,停下\N{\fs90}Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.59,0:49:11.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 哈蒙德\N{\fs90}Hammond! Hammond!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.28,0:49:17.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,咋啦\N{\fs90}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.72,0:49:21.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,大壮游 明年还可以再搞一次\N{\fs90}Grand Tour. We can do it again next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.99,0:49:24.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,怎么样 明年要不要再搞一次\N{\fs90}Next year? Do it again next year?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.57,0:49:29.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,你不光是把我俩\N{\fs90}Not only did you knock us into
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.51,0:49:32.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,晃进了威尼斯的污水里\N{\fs90}the sewage-infested waters of Venice...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.46,0:49:35.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,你还把我们给你的礼物拦腰折断\N{\fs90}you cut the present we gave you in half.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.92,0:49:37.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,不等一会 没有 \N{\fs90}No, hang on a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.12,0:49:39.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,它就像是一个只有两块的拼图一样 \N{\fs90} No, it was only like a two-piece jigsaw puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.29,0:49:40.48,字幕,,0,0,0,, 我又把它拼起来了\N{\fs90} and I put it back together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.50,0:49:41.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看 就在那 \N{\fs90}Look, there it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.69,0:49:42.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,怎么样 完好如初吧\N{\fs90}See? Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.82,0:49:44.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 干嘛\N{\fs90}-Hammond? -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.10,0:49:48.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,人家艺术馆没人会为了把艺术品搬上楼\N{\fs90}Art galleries do not saw artworks in half
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.40,0:49:50.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,而把它们锯成两半 你个智障\N{\fs90}just to get them up the stairs, you moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.74,0:49:52.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,总之 听着 在我们进入下一个板块之前\N{\fs90}Anyway, listen, before we move on,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.60,0:49:54.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能再多说几句关于阿斯顿马丁的吗\N{\fs90}can I just say something about that Aston Martin?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.46,0:49:56.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是为了惹你俩生气 我是真心的\N{\fs90}Not to wind you two up. I genuinely mean this.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.88,0:49:58.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,这真是辆好车\N{\fs90}It's an amazing car.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.34,0:50:00.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,我承认它方向盘是方的\N{\fs90}I know the steering wheel is square.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.32,0:50:01.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,-它还是棕色的 -没错\N{\fs90}-And it was brown -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.88,0:50:03.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,内饰也不漂亮\N{\fs90}And I know the interior wasn't very nice,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.99,0:50:05.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是它真的打动我了\N{\fs90}but, genuinely, it's affected me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.84,0:50:07.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我回来之后它\N{\fs90}It's been living up here
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.49,0:50:08.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,它就一直在我脑海中挥之不去\N{\fs90}ever since I got back.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.78,0:50:10.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,哎说到脑海啊\N{\fs90}And talking of up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.54,0:50:14.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在应该是明星脑碰脑时间了\N{\fs90}it's now time to play Celebrity Brain Crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.36,0:50:24.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,是时候让明星们\N{\fs90}Yes, it's time for a top celebrity
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.39,0:50:26.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我们可怕的测试中\N{\fs90}to try their hand at our
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.29,0:50:28.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,展现他们的技巧\N{\fs90}fearsome test of skill,co-ordination
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.92,0:50:30.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,协调性和观察力\N{\fs90} and observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.70,0:50:32.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要解释一下\N{\fs90}Now, so far, I should explain,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.87,0:50:36.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,目前没有明星成功踏进我们的帐篷\N{\fs90}no celebrity has actually made it to the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.13,0:50:38.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 他们都死了\N{\fs90}No, they've all died.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.54,0:50:41.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这次让我们一起祈祷吧\N{\fs90}Yes, but our fingers are crossed for this week,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.27,0:50:44.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这次的嘉宾是位巨星\N{\fs90}because our guest is a huge star.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.20,0:50:47.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,他参演过碟中谍\N{\fs90}You'll have seen him in Mission Impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.23,0:50:48.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,星际迷航\N{\fs90}Star Trek,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.26,0:50:49.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,僵尸肖恩\N{\fs90}Shaun Of The Dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.32,0:50:51.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,热血警探\N{\fs90}Hot Fuzz,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.58,0:50:54.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,他今天会在这谈论他新电影\N{\fs90}and he's here to talk about his new movie -
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.12,0:50:56.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,由斯皮尔伯格导演的 一级玩家\N{\fs90}Spielberg movie - Ready Player One .
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.35,0:50:59.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们 西蒙 佩吉\N{\fs90}Ladies and gentlemen, we've got Simon Pegg!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.80,0:51:04.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,他就在那\N{\fs90}And there he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.47,0:51:07.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,他就在那\N{\fs90}There he is, ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.18,0:51:08.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,和他的可爱多\N{\fs90}with his Cornetto.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.80,0:51:09.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,永远都有一个甜筒\N{\fs90}Always a Cornetto.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.88,0:51:11.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,他和外星人干过仗\N{\fs90}He's battled aliens,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.93,0:51:13.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,和僵尸打过架\N{\fs90}he's battled zombies,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.42,0:51:15.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以他应该能顺利地\N{\fs90}he should have no problem at all
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.45,0:51:17.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这美丽小镇溜达吧\N{\fs90}with a short stroll through this pretty little town.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.56,0:51:20.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,他电影里我最喜欢 保罗\N{\fs90}Of all his films, it's Paul that I like best.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.11,0:51:21.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,-对 那是一部很出色的电影\N{\fs90}-I think that stands out.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.22,0:51:23.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,-保罗简直是泰迪熊的祖先\N{\fs90}Paul was the forerunner of Ted, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.62,0:51:25.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错 -它先出来的\N{\fs90}-It was -It was first. It came first.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.44,0:51:28.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,我最喜欢热血警探 那打斗场面\N{\fs90}Hot Fuzz  It's Hot Fuzz for me, just because of the fight scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.59,0:51:30.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,他来了 他到桥上了\N{\fs90}There he is He's on the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.68,0:51:33.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,看起来海鸥要找他麻烦\N{\fs90}- It looks like he's being hassled by seagulls.
